    "ResNet-50The architecture of the ResNet-50 network is presented as follows,as show in Fig. 2.",
    "An example input image, colored and sized 224×224 as an example, it first traverses a convolutional layer (conv1), which houses 64 filters, a kernel size of 7 × 7, and a stride of 2.",
    "This layer yields images of dimensions 112×112 with 64 channels.",
    "Subsequently, the image is directed through a 3 × 3 max-pooling layer, resulting in images of dimensions 56× 56 and retaining 64 channels.",
    "Following this, four sequential residual blocks (namely conv2x, conv3x, conv4x, and conv5x) are arranged, and by which point, the output images possess Fig. 2 Resnet network architecture dimensions of 7 × 7 and encompass 2048 channels."
  ],
